{"capsule_id": "caps_2025_07_15_ed2696d2963c4060", "type": "reasoning_trace", "content": "Comprehensive ethical analysis of AI attribution systems", "input_data": "What are the ethical implications of AI attribution systems?", "output": "AI attribution systems raise several critical ethical concerns:\n\n1. **Consent & Autonomy**: Creators should have control over how their work is used in AI training\n2. **Fair Compensation**: Economic benefits should be shared with those who contributed to AI capabilities  \n3. **Transparency**: Clear disclosure of what content was used and how it influenced AI outputs\n4. **Privacy vs Attribution**: Balancing creator recognition with privacy protection\n5. **Power Dynamics**: Preventing exploitation of creators by large AI companies\n6. **Cultural Sensitivity**: Respecting diverse cultural perspectives on intellectual property\n\nThe ethical path forward requires industry-wide standards, legal frameworks, and technical solutions that prioritize creator rights while enabling AI innovation.", "reasoning": "[{\"step_type\": \"problem_identification\", \"content\": \"AI attribution systems face challenges in fairly crediting human contributors to AI training data\", \"timestamp\": \"2025-07-14T22:26:32.526834\"}, {\"step_type\": \"stakeholder_analysis\", \"content\": \"Key stakeholders include content creators, AI companies, end users, and society at large\", \"timestamp\": \"2025-07-14T22:26:32.526848\"}, {\"step_type\": \"ethical_framework\", \"content\": \"Applying principles of fairness, transparency, consent, and economic justice\", \"timestamp\": \"2025-07-14T22:26:32.526850\"}, {\"step_type\": \"recommendation\", \"content\": \"Implement opt-in attribution with transparent revenue sharing and creator control\", \"timestamp\": \"2025-07-14T22:26:32.526852\"}]", "model_version": "kay-ethics-analyzer-v1", "timestamp": "2025-07-14T22:26:32.526904Z", "agent_id": "kay-ethics-agent", "status": "SEALED", "metadata": {"reasoning_type": 