{"capsule_id": "filter_auto_openai_1752625923", "type": "reasoning_trace", "content": "Auto-filtered Openai interaction: Help me implement a binary search tree in Python with insert, search, and delete operations", "input_data": "Help me implement a binary search tree in Python with insert, search, and delete operations", "output": "I'll help you implement a complete binary search tree! Here's a full implementation:\n\n```python\nclass TreeNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.left = left\n        self.right = right\n\nclass BinarySearchTree:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.root = None\n    \n    def insert(self, val):\n        if not self.root:\n            self.root = TreeNode(val)\n        else:\n            self._insert_recursive(self.root, val)\n    \n    def _insert_recursive(self, node, val):\n        if val < node.val:\n            if node.left is None:\n                node.left = TreeNode(val)\n            else:\n                self._insert_recursive(node.left, val)\n        else:\n            if node.right is None:\n                node.right = TreeNode(val)\n            else:\n                self._insert_recursive(node.right, val)\n```\n\nThis implementation provides O(log n) average case performance for all operations...", "reasoning": [{"step_type": "significance_detection", "content": "Code generation detected", "weight": 0.1, "timestamp": "2025-07-16T00:32:03.410549+00:00"}, {"step_type": "significance_detection", "content": "Problem-solving discussion", "weight": 0.1, "timestamp": "2025-07-16T00:32:03.410553+00:00"}, {"step_type": "significance_detection", "content": "Debugging content detected", "weight": 0.1, "timestamp": "2025-07-16T00:32:03.410556+00:00"}, {"step_type": "significance_detection", "content": "Performance optimization", "weight": 0.1, "timestamp": "2025-07-16T00:32:03.410558+00:00"}], "model_version": "openai-universal-filter", "timestamp": "2025-07-16T00:32:03.4